tracks.fmtDetailValue_Dbxref: function(dbxref){ var items = []; var output = 'N/A'; var isArray; if(dbxref.constructor === Array){ for(i = 0; i < dbxref.length; i++){ ref = dbxref[i].split(':'); if(ref[0] == "GeneID"){ items.push('Entrez Gene: ' + ref[1] + ''); } else if(ref[0] == "Xenbase"){ items.push('Xenbase Gene Page'); } else if(ref[0] == "Genbank"){ items.push('Genbank');}}} else{ ref = dbxref.split(':'); if(ref[0] == "GeneID"){ items.push('Entrez Gene: ' + ref[1] + ''); } else if(ref[0] == "Xenbase"){ items.push('Xenbase Gene Page'); } else if(ref[0] == "Genbank"){ items.push('Genbank');}} if(items.length != 0){ output = items.join(", ");} return output;}

tracks.key: GS-Stage 10.5
tracks.label: gs_stage10_5

metadata.Info:
This track was generated by running ChromHMM on data from
multiple source including H3K27me3, H3K36me3, H3K4me1,
H3K4me3, H3K9ac, H3K9me2, H3K9me3,H4K20me3, p300, RNAPII
and TLE ChIP-Seq data. We merged the different data sources
into one track and color coded them based on UCSC genome
segmentation track colors, including promoter, poised enhancer,
active enhancer, heterochromatin,transcribed region, and
polycomb segments.

style.color: function(feature){ if(feature.get('type')=='Polycomb') { return '#808080';} else if(feature.get('type')=='Poised'){ return '#800080';} else if(feature.get('type')=='ActiveEnhancer'){ return '#ffff00';} else if(feature.get('type')=='Transcribed'){ return '#008000';} else if(feature.get('type')=='Promoter'){ return '#ff0000';} else if(feature.get('type')=='Heterochromatin'){ return '#c0c0c0';}}

H3K4me1, H3K4me3, P300, H3K27me3, H3K9me2, H3K9me3, and H4K20me3 at stage 16.

tracks.key: Pseudogenes
tracks.label: hybrid_pseudo

metadata.Info:
This pseudogene track includes both processed pseudogenes (colored green)
and NCBI pseudogenes (colored yellow). The processed pseudogenes are
generated by aligning protein sequences to genome sequences,
merging adjacent homologies, and realigning protein sequences
to genome sequences using fasta. The method was presented
in two papers by Zhang et al (2002 and 2003).

metadata.<span name='001'>Description:
This track shows guide RNA sequences, including PAM sites (NGG),
for coding sequences. Feature info also includes T7 or SP6
promoter based oligo sequences for expressing the sgRNA in a
plasmid. The distinct primers are TAATACGACTCACTATA
for T7 and ATTTAGGTGACACTATA for SP6.
metadata.Data source:

publication can be found here: Paper. To cite this data

tracks.fmtDetailValue_Dbxref: function(dbxref){ var items = []; var output = 'N/A'; var isArray; if(dbxref.constructor === Array){ for(i = 0; i < dbxref.length; i++){ ref = dbxref[i].split(':'); if(ref[0] == "GeneID"){ items.push('Entrez Gene: ' + ref[1] + ''); } else if(ref[0] == "Xenbase"){ items.push('Xenbase Gene Page'); } else if(ref[0] == "Genbank"){ items.push('Genbank');} else if(ref[0] == "PubMed"){ items.push('PubMed'); } else if(ref[0] == "miRBase"){ items.push('miRBase');}}} else{ ref = dbxref.split(':'); if(ref[0] == "GeneID"){ items.push('Entrez Gene: ' + ref[1] + ''); } else if(ref[0] == "Xenbase"){ items.push('Xenbase Gene Page'); } else if(ref[0] == "Genbank"){ items.push('Genbank');} else if(ref[0] == "PubMed"){items.push('PubMed');} else if(ref[0] == "miRBase"){ items.push('miRBase');}} if(items.length != 0){ output = items.join(", ");} return output;}
